      "content": "it's not about \"new passions.\" that's just a platitude. when your entire purpose was dedicated to this pursuit, there is no \"elsewhere.\" it's like being an eye that realized it's blind. the person I was is dead, and the person I'm left with is a hollow shell of a lie. i look at the world and i just see the futility of it all. everything is just noise and wasted effort. there is no meaning in trying to rebuild something that was never real in the first place. i just feel so incredibly finished.",
